spider man: into the spider verse
summary: Okay so a lot of people are upset or worried about how there are a bunch of other characters in Spider-Verse, and they think...
body:
Okay so a lot of people are upset or worried about how there are a bunch of other characters in Spider-Verse, and they think it’s gonna take away from Miles’ movie. I had my concerns too, but the movie turned out to be all about Miles.

I saw the movie yesterday, and I was really happy about it because it was HIS movie. The other spider-people, minus Peter and kind of Gwen, are treated as side characters. The story focuses on Miles and his journey of becoming Spider-Man.

Peter is the exception to being a side character because he’s the one mentoring Miles, but he doesn’t overshadow Miles. He’s there to help his journey along and teach him, but Miles is always the main focus of the story.

The other spider-people are there just to have fun with the concept, so don’t worry about them stealing Miles’ spotlight. The movie from start to finish is just about Miles and his struggles with gaining these powers and trying to save the world. The other spiders are just along for the ride, and they’re not in the movie for very long either. They don’t even really show up until like….a little bit before the final battle?? They really don’t steal from Miles’s spotlight.

summary: can we pls stop treating Peter Parker like an infant??? I always see these weird posts(usually about him and Tony) and it’s not...
body:
can we pls stop treating Peter Parker like an infant??? I always see these weird posts(usually about him and Tony) and it’s not even wholesome or anything, it’s about Tony helping him with very basic life skills, or portrays Peter as an idiot who can’t do anything for himself… Peter Parker is a genius who designed his own web shooters, dealt with the death of his parents and his Uncle Ben all while balancing being at an extremely difficult school for the brightest kids.


I could go on and on.


Yes he’s a teenager. Yes he needs help. But not that much more than every one else, and he’s not a child. Stop acting like he is.
